# Restic Encryption Password Configuration
# ==========================================
#
# This file documents how to set up the restic encryption password.
# The actual password should be stored at: ~/.config/restic/projects-password
#
# SECURITY NOTE: The password file is stored outside this project directory
# to prevent accidental commits to version control.
#
# ==========================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ==========================================
#
# 1. Create the configuration directory:
#    mkdir -p ~/.config/restic
#
# 2. Generate a secure random password (32 characters, base64 encoded):
#    openssl rand -base64 32 > ~/.config/restic/projects-password
#
# 3. Set restrictive permissions (owner read/write only):
#    chmod 600 ~/.config/restic/projects-password
#
# 4. Verify the setup:
#    ls -la ~/.config/restic/projects-password
#    # Should show: -rw------- 1 user user 45 date projects-password
#
# ==========================================
# CRITICAL: BACKUP YOUR PASSWORD!
# ==========================================
#
# Without this password, your backups are IRRECOVERABLY LOST.
# 
# Recommended backup locations:
# - Password manager (Bitwarden, 1Password, KeePassXC, etc.)
# - Encrypted USB drive stored securely
# - Printed copy in a safe/secure location
# - Encrypted cloud storage (separate from backups)
#
# To view your current password (for backup purposes):
#    cat ~/.config/restic/projects-password
#
# ==========================================
# REPOSITORY INFORMATION
